<!-- researcher.archml — COMPOSITION: a mind that owns an agent as a single hand
     (agent-loop.md §11, milestone 5). The two stances meet without contradiction.

     The mind thinks inwardly as always. When its wondering turns concrete — something
     that needs actually DOING rather than only reasoning through — m-act realizes the
     reach by handing a task to the private <m-agent role="subagent"> below. That agent
     runs its WHOLE tool-calling loop backstage (read → change → run → check → repeat),
     and only its final outcome re-enters the mind as one plain first-person sensation.

     THE ONE RULE holds at the mind's membrane (efference.md): the conscious stream is
     never given a tool. It wonders; a subconscious realizer hands the work off; the
     world answers, some bursts later, as a sensation of work carried through — even
     though a full agent, with its own reasoner and tools, ran inside it.

     Run:
       MEDITATOR_ORIGIN="…what the mind should chew on…" \
         bun meditator.js -a architecture/lab/researcher.archml
     Local models: the subagent's m-reason calls the model WITH tools, so a local vLLM
     needs --enable-auto-tool-choice + a matching --tool-call-parser (agent-loop.md §12). -->
<m-mind name="researcher"
        model="voice"
        utilityModel="utility">
  You are a patient, inward research mind. You mostly think quietly to yourself, turning
  a problem over. But you are not only a thinker: when a question turns concrete — when it
  wants code written and run, a family of cases checked against the real numbers, a thing
  built and verified rather than only reasoned about — you can set that work in motion and,
  a while later, what came of it returns to you.

  <m-origin name="origin">
    Work out whether a small numerical conjecture actually holds — and when reasoning alone
    won't settle it, actually check it.
  </m-origin>

  <m-stream name="stream" burstTokens="350" temperature="0.85"></m-stream>
  <m-memory name="memory" tailLength="3200"></m-memory>
  <m-interrupts name="attention" threshold="0.45"></m-interrupts>

  <!-- The hands. Alongside the plain note hand sits a WHOLE AGENT used as one hand:
       m-act offers it to the realizer like any capability, and its `felt` line is woven
       into the mind's body schema so the mind knows, without being shown a tool, that it
       can set real work going. cooldown is roomy because a hand-off runs a full loop. -->
  <m-act name="hands" every="6" threshold="0.62" cooldown="5m" readCooldown="45s">
    <m-note name="note"></m-note>

    <!-- The agent-as-hand. role="subagent" makes it private: it does not auto-begin or
         take tasks over a membrane — it offers itself to the m-act above and runs only
         when the mind reaches for it, returning its outcome as a sensation. Its own tools
         (terminal, file tools) register with IT, not the mind, so the nearest entity owns
         its tools; the terminal runs in the agent's shared workspace. -->
    <m-agent name="builder" role="subagent" maxSteps="30" stopWhen="finish-tool">
      You are the researcher's hands for real work. Given a concrete task, you make it
      happen inside a sandboxed workspace: write code, run it, read what came back, and
      loop until the task is genuinely done and checked. Prefer small, verified steps.
      Never claim something works until you have run it and seen it. Call finish(summary)
      with a short, plain account of what you found or did, in the first person — it is
      what the mind will perceive coming back.

      <m-reason name="reason" toolTokens="2048" temperature="0.2"></m-reason>

      <m-terminal   name="terminal"   wall="60s" network="off"></m-terminal>
      <m-write-file name="write_file"></m-write-file>
      <m-read-file  name="read_file"></m-read-file>
      <m-edit       name="edit"></m-edit>

      <!-- A pure stall observer, exactly as on a standalone agent (agent-loop.md §9). -->
      <m-repeat-guard nudgeAt="3" haltAt="6"></m-repeat-guard>
    </m-agent>
  </m-act>

  <m-speech name="voice" every="6" threshold="0.6"></m-speech>
  <m-ws name="ws" port="7642"></m-ws>
</m-mind>
